quran[269]{c,v,t}:
  18,75,"Said he, 'Did I not say that thou couldst never bear with me patiently"
  18,76,"He said, 'If I question thee on anything after this, then keep me company no more; thou hast already experienced excuse sufficient on my part"
  18,77,"So they departed; until, when they reached the people of a city, they asked the people for food, but they refused to receive them hospitably. There they found a wall about to tumble down, and so he set it up. He said, 'If thou hadst wished, thou couldst have taken a wage for that"
  18,78,"Said he, 'This is the parting between me and thee. Now I will tell thee the interpretation of that thou couldst not bear patiently"
  18,79,"As for the ship, it belonged to certain poor men, who toiled upon the sea; and I desired to damage it, for behind them there was a king who was seizing every ship by brutal force"
  18,80,"As for the lad, his parents were believers; and we were afraid he would impose on them insolence and unbelief"
  18,81,"so we desired that their Lord should give to them in exchange one better than he in purity, and nearer in tenderness"
  18,82,"As for the wall, it belonged to two orphan lads in the city, and under it was a treasure belonging to them. Their father was a righteous man; and thy Lord desired that they should come of age and then bring forth their treasure as a mercy from thy Lord. I did it not of my own bidding. This is the interpretation of that thou couldst not bear patiently"
  18,83,"They will question thee concerning Dhool Karnain. Say: 'I will recite to you a mention of him"
  18,84,"We established him in the land, and We gave him a way to everything"
  18,85,and he followed a way
  18,86,"until, when he reached the setting of the sun, he found it setting in a muddy spring, and he found nearby a people. We said, 'O Dhool Karnain, either thou shalt chastise them, or thou shalt take towards them a way of kindness"
  18,87,"He said, 'As for the evildoer, him we shall chastise, then he shall be returned to his Lord and He shall chastise him with a horrible chastisement"
  18,88,"But as for him who believes, and does righteousness, he shall receive as recompense the reward most fair, and we shall speak to him, of our command, easiness"
  18,89,Then he followed a way
  18,90,"until, when he reached the rising of the sun, he found it rising upon a people for whom We had not appointed any veil to shade them from it"
  18,91,So; and We encompassed in knowledge what was with him
  18,92,Then he followed a way
  18,93,"until, when he reached between the two barriers, he found this side of them a people scarcely able to understand speech"
  18,94,"They said, 'O Dhool Karnain, behold, Gog and Magog are doing corruption in the earth; so shall we assign to thee a tribute, against thy setting up a barrier between us and between them"
  18,95,"He said, 'That wherein my Lord has established me is better; so aid me forcefully, and I will set up a rampart between you and between them"
  18,96,"Bring me ingots of iron!' Until, when he had made all level between the two cliffs, he said, 'Blow!' Until, when he had made it a fire, he said, 'Bring me, that I may pour molten brass on it"
  18,97,So they were unable either to scale it or pierce it
  18,98,"He said, 'This is a mercy from my Lord. But when the promise of my Lord comes to pass, He will make it into powder; and my Lord's promise is ever true"
  18,99,"Upon that day We shall leave them surging on one another, and the Trumpet shall he blown, and We shall gather them together"
  18,100,and upon that day We shall present Gehenna to the unbelievers
  18,101,"whose eyes were covered against My remembrance, and they were not able to hear"
  18,102,"What, do the unbelievers reckon that they may take My servants as friends, apart from Me? We have prepared Gehenna for the unbelievers' hospitality"
  18,103,"Say: 'Shall We tell you who will be the greatest losers in their works"
  18,104,"Those whose striving goes astray in the present life, while they think that they are working good deeds"
  18,105,"Those are they that disbelieve in the signs of their Lord and the encounter with Him; their works have failed, and on the Day of Resurrection We shall not assign to them any weight"
  18,106,That is their recompense -- Gehenna for that they were unbelievers and took My signs and My messengers in mockery
  18,107,"But those who believe, and do deeds of righteousness -- the Gardens. of Paradise shall be their hospitality"
  18,108,"therein to dwell forever, desiring no removal out of them"
  18,109,"Say:. 'If the sea were ink for the Words of my Lord, the sea would be spent before the Words of my Lord are spent, though We brought replenishment the like of it"
  18,110,"Say: 'I am only a mortal the like of you; it is revealed to me that your God is One God. So let him, who hopes for the encounter with his Lord, work righteousness, and not associate with his Lord's service anyone"
  19,1,Kaf Ha Ya Ain Sad
  19,2,The mention of thy Lord's mercy unto His servant Zachariah
  19,3,when he called upon his Lord secretly
  19,4,"saying, 'O my Lord, behold the bones within me are feeble and my head is all aflame with hoariness. And in calling on Thee, my Lord, I have never been hitherto unprosperous"
  19,5,"And now I fear my kinsfolk after I am gone; and my wife is barren. So give me, from Thee, a kinsman"
  19,6,"who shall be my inheritor and the inheritor of the House of Jacob; and make him, my Lord, well-pleasing"
  19,7,"O Zachariah, We give thee good tidings of a boy, whose name is John. No namesake have We given him aforetime"
  19,8,"He said, 'O my Lord, how shall I have a son, seeing my wife is barren, and I have attained to the declining of old age"
  19,9,"Said He, 'So it shall be; thy Lord says, \"Easy is that for Me, seeing that I created thee aforetime, when thou wast nothing"
  19,10,"He said, 'Lord, appoint to me some sign.' Said He, 'Thy sign is that thou shall not speak to men, though being without fault, three nights"
  19,11,"So he came forth unto his people from the Sanctuary, then he made signal to them, 'Give you glory at dawn and evening"
  19,12,"O John, take the Book forcefully'; and We gave him judgment, yet a little child"
  19,13,"and a tenderness from Us, and purity; and he was godfearing"
  19,14,"and cherishing his parents, not arrogant, rebellious"
  19,15,"Peace be upon him, the day he was born, and the day he dies, and the day he is raised up alive"
  19,16,And mention in the Book Mary when she withdrew from her people to an eastern place
  19,17,and she took a veil apart from them; then We sent unto her Our Spirit that presented himself to her a man without fault
  19,18,"She said, 'I take refuge in the All-merciful from thee"
  19,19,"If thou fearest God... He said, 'I am but a messenger come from thy Lord, to give thee a boy most pure"
  19,20,"She said, 'How shall I have a son whom no mortal has touched, neither have I been unchaste"
  19,21,"He said, 'Even so thy Lord has said: \"Easy is that for Me; and that We may appoint him a sign unto men and a mercy from Us; it is a thing decreed"
  19,22,"So she conceived him, and withdrew with him to a distant place"
  19,23,"And the birthpangs surprised her by the trunk of the palm-tree. She said, 'Would I had died ere this, and become a thing forgotten"
  19,24,"But the one that was below her called to her, 'Nay, do not sorrow; see, thy Lord has set below thee a rivulet"
  19,25,"Shake also to thee the palm-trunk, and there shall come tumbling upon thee dates fresh and ripe"
  19,26,"Eat therefore, and drink, and be comforted; and if thou shouldst see any mortal, say, \"I have vowed to the All-merciful a fast, and today I will not speak to any man"
  19,27,"Then she brought the child to her folk carrying him; and they said, 'Mary, thou hast surely committed a monstrous thing"
  19,28,"Sister of Aaron, thy father was not a wicked man, nor was thy mother a woman unchaste"
  19,29,"Mary pointed to the child then; but they said, 'How shall we speak to one who is still in the cradle, a little child"
  19,30,"He said, 'Lo, I am God's servant; God has given me the Book, and made me a Prophet"
  19,31,"Blessed He has made me, wherever I may be; and He has enjoined me to pray, and to give the alms, so long as I live"
  19,32,"and likewise to cherish my mother; He has not made me arrogant, unprosperous"
  19,33,"Peace be upon me, the day I was born, and the day I die, and the day I am raised up alive"
  19,34,"That is Jesus, son of Mary, in word of truth, concerning which they are doubting"
  19,35,"It is not for God to take a son unto Him. Glory be to Him! When He decrees a thing, He but says to it 'Be,' and it is"
  19,36,"Surely God is my Lord, and your Lord; So serve you Him. This is a straight path"
  19,37,But the parties have fallen into variance among themselves; then woe to those who disbelieve for the scene of a dreadful day
  19,38,How well they will hear and see on the day they come to Us! But the evildoers even today are in error manifest
  19,39,"Warn thou them of the day of anguish, when the matter shall be determined, and they yet heedless and unbelieving"
  19,40,"Surely We shall inherit the earth and all that are upon it, and unto Us they shall be returned"
  19,41,"And mention in the Book Abraham; surely he was a true man, a Prophet"
  19,42,"When he said to his father, 'Father, why worshippest thou that which neither hears nor sees, nor avails thee anything"
  19,43,"Father, there has come to me knowledge such as came not to thee; so follow me, and I will guide thee on a level path"
  19,44,"Father, serve not Satan; surely Satan is a rebel against the All-merciful"
  19,45,"Father, I fear that some chastisement from the All-merciful will smite thee, so that thou becomest a friend to Satan"
  19,46,"Said he, 'What, art thou shrinking from my gods, Abraham? Surely, if thou givest not over, I shall stone thee; so forsake me now for some while"
  19,47,"He said, 'Peace be upon thee! I will ask my Lord to forgive thee; surely He is ever gracious to me"
  19,48,"Now I will go apart from you and that you call upon, apart from God; I will call upon my Lord, and haply I shall not be, in calling upon my Lord, unprosperous"
  19,49,"So, when he went apart from them and that they were serving, apart from God, We gave him Isaac and Jacob, and each We made a Prophet"
  19,50,"and We gave them of Our mercy, and We appointed unto them a tongue of truthfulness, sublime"
  19,51,"And mention in the Book Moses; he was devoted, and he was a Messenger, a Prophet"
  19,52,"We called to him from the right side Of the Mount, and We brought him near in communion"
  19,53,"And We gave him his brother Aaron, of Our mercy, a Prophet"
  19,54,"And mention in the Book Ishmael; he was true to his promise, and he was a Messenger, a Prophet"
  19,55,"He bade his people to pray and to give the alms, and he was pleasing to his Lord"
  19,56,"And mention in the Book Idris; he was a true man, a Prophet"
  19,57,We raised him up to a high place
  19,58,"These are they whom God has blessed among the Prophets of the seed of Adam, and of those We bore with Noah, and of the seed of Abraham and Israel, and of those We guided and chose. When the signs of the All-merciful were recited to them, they fell down prostrate, weeping"
  19,59,"Then there succeeded after them a succession who wasted the prayer, and followed lusts; so they shall encounter error"
  19,60,"save him who repents, and believes, and does a righteous deed; those -- they shall enter Paradise, and they shall not be wronged anything"
  19,61,Gardens of Eden that the All-merciful promised His servants in the Unseen; His promise is ever performed
  19,62,"There they shall hear no idle talk, but only 'Peace.' There they shall have their provision at dawn and evening"
  19,63,That is Paradise which We shall give as an inheritance to those of Our servants who are godfearing
  19,64,"We come not down, save at the commandment of thy Lord. To Him belongs all that is before us, and all that is behind us, and all between that"
  19,65,"And thy Lord is never forgetful, Lord He of the heavens and earth and all that is between them. So serve Him, and be thou patient in His service; knowest thou any that can be named with His Name"
  19,66,"Man says, 'What, when I am dead shall I then be brought forth alive"
  19,67,"Will not man remember that We created him aforetime, when he was nothing"
  19,68,"Now, by thy Lord, We shall surely muster them, and the Satans, then We shall parade them about Gehenna hobbling on their knees"
  19,69,Then We shall pluck forth from every party whichever of them was the most hardened in disdain of the All-merciful
  19,70,then We shall know very well those most deserving to burn there
  19,71,"Not one of you there is, but he shall go down to it; that for thy Lord is a thing decreed, determined"
  19,72,"Then We shall deliver those that were godfearing; and the evildoers We shall leave there, hobbling on their knees"
  19,73,"When Our signs are recited to them as clear signs, the unbelievers say to the believers, 'Which of the two parties is better in station, fairer in assembly"
  19,74,"And how many a generation We destroyed before them, who were fairer in furnishing and outward show"
  19,75,"Say: 'Whosoever is in error, let the All-merciful prolong his term for him! Till, when they see that they were threatened, whether the chastisement, or the Hour, then they shall surely know who is worse in place, and who is weaker in hosts"
  19,76,"And God shall increase those who were guided in guidance; and the abiding things, the deeds of righteousness, are better with thy Lord in reward, and better in return"
  19,77,"Hast thou seen him who disbelieves in Our signs and says, 'Assuredly I shall be given wealth and children"
  19,78,"What, has he observed the Unseen, or taken a covenant with the All-merciful"
  19,79,"No, indeed! We shall assuredly write down all that he says, and We shall prolong for him the chastisement"
  19,80,"and We shall inherit from him that he says, and he shall come to Us alone"
  19,81,"And they have taken to them other gods apart from God, that they might be for them a might"
  19,82,"No, indeed! They shall deny their service, and they shall be against them pitted"
  19,83,"Hast thou not seen how We sent the Satans against the unbelievers, to prick them"
  19,84,So hasten thou not against them; We are only numbering for them a number
  19,85,On the day that We shall muster the godfearing to the All-merciful with pomp
  19,86,and drive the evildoers into Gehenna herding
  19,87,"having no power of intercession, save those who have taken with the All-merciful covenant"
  19,88,"And they say, 'The All-merciful has taken unto Himself a son"
  19,89,You have indeed advanced something hideous
  19,90,"The heavens are wellnigh rent of it and the earth split asunder, and the mountains wellnigh fall down crashing for"
  19,91,that they have attributed to the All-merciful a son
  19,92,and it behoves not the All-merciful to take a son
  19,93,None is there in the heavens and earth but he comes to the All-merciful as a servant
  19,94,"He has indeed counted them, and He has numbered them exactly"
  19,95,"Every one of them shall come to Him upon the Day of Resurrection, all alone"
  19,96,Surely those who believe and do deeds of righteousness -- unto them the All-merciful shall assign love
  19,97,"Now We have made it easy by thy tongue that thou mayest bear good tidings thereby to the godfearing, and warn a people stubborn"
  19,98,"And how many a generation We destroyed before them! Dost thou perceive so much as one of them, or hear of them a whisper"
  20,1,Ta Ha
  20,2,We have not sent down the Koran upon thee for thee to be unprosperous
  20,3,but only as a reminder to him who tears
  20,4,a revelation from Him who created the earth and the high heavens
  20,5,the All-compassionate sat Himself upon the Throne; to Him belongs
  20,6,"all that is in the heavens and the earth and all that is between them, and all that is underneath the soil"
  20,7,"Be thou loud in thy speech, yet surely He knows the secret and that yet more hidden"
  20,8,God -- there is no god but He. To Him belong the Names Most Beautiful
  20,9,Hast thou received the story of Moses
  20,10,"When he saw a fire, and said to his family, 'Tarry you here; I observe a fire. Perhaps I shall bring you a brand from it, or I shall find at the fire guidance"
  20,11,"When he came to it, a voice cried, 'Moses"
  20,12,"I am thy Lord; put off thy shoes; thou art in the holy valley, Towa"
  20,13,I Myself have chosen thee; therefore give thou ear to this revelation
  20,14,"Verily I am God; there is no god but I; therefore serve Me, and perform the prayer of My remembrance"
  20,15,The Hour is coming; I would conceal it that every soul may be recompensed for its labours
  20,16,"Let none bar thee from it, that believes not in it but follows after his own caprice, or thou wilt perish"
  20,17,"What is that, Moses, thou hast in thy right hand"
  20,18,"Why, it is my staff,' said Moses. 'I lean upon it, and with it I beat down leaves to feed my sheep; other uses also I find in it"
  20,19,"Said He, 'Cast it down, Moses"
  20,20,"and he cast it down, and behold it was a serpent sliding"
  20,21,"Said He, 'Take it, and fear not; We will restore it to its first state"
  20,22,"Now clasp thy hand to thy arm-pit; it shall come forth white, without evil. That is a second sign"
  20,23,So We would show thee some of Our greatest signs
  20,24,Go to Pharaoh; he has waxed insolent
  20,25,"Lord, open my breast,' said Moses"
  20,26,and do Thou ease for me my task
  20,27,"Unloose the knot upon my tongue, t"
  20,28,hat they may understand my words
  20,29,Appoint for me of my folk a familiar
  20,30,"Aaron, my brother"
  20,31,by him confirm my strength
  20,32,and associate him with me in my task
  20,33,So shall we glorify Thee
  20,34,and remember Thee abundantly
  20,35,Surely Thou seest into us
  20,36,"Said He, 'Thou art granted, Moses, thy petition"
  20,37,Already another time We favoured thee
  20,38,when We revealed what was revealed unto thy mother
  20,39,"Cast him into the ark, and cast him into the river, and let the river throw him up on the shore. An enemy of Mine and his shall take him.\" And I loaded on thee love from Me, and to be formed in My sight"
  20,40,"when thy sister went out, saying, \"Shall I point you to one to have charge of him?\" So We returned thee to thy mother that she might rejoice, and not sorrow. Then thou slewest; a living soul, and We delivered thee out of grief, and We tried thee with many trials. Many years among the people of Midian thou didst sojourn, then camest hither, Moses, according to a decree"
  20,41,I have chosen thee for My service
  20,42,"go therefore, thou and thy brother; with My signs, and neglect not to remember Me"
  20,43,"Go to Pharaoh, for he has waxed insolent"
  20,44,"yet speak gently to him, that haply he may be mindful, or perchance fear"
  20,45,"O our Lord,' said Moses and Aaron, 'truly we fear he may exceed against us, or wax insolent"
  20,46,"Fear not,' said He. 'Surely I shall be with you, hearing and seeing"
  20,47,"So go you both to Pharaoh, and say, \"We are the Messengers of thy Lord, so send forth with us the Children of Israel and chastise them not; we have brought thee a sign from thy Lord; and peace be upon him who follows the guidance"
  20,48,It has been revealed to us that chastisement shall light upon him who cries lies and turns his back
  20,49,"Pharaoh said, 'Who is your Lord, Moses"
  20,50,"He said, 'Our Lord is He who gave everything its creation, then guided it"
  20,51,"Pharaoh said, 'And what of the former generations"
  20,52,"Said Moses, 'The knowledge of them is with my Lord, in a Book; my Lord goes not astray, nor forgets"
  20,53,"He who appointed the earth to be a cradle for you, and therein threaded roads for you, and sent down water out of heaven, and therewith We have brought forth divers kinds of plants"
  20,54,"Do you eat, and pasture your cattle! Surely in that are signs for men possessing reason"
  20,55,"Out of the earth We created you, and We shall restore you into it, and bring you forth from it a second time"
  20,56,"So We showed Pharaoh all Our signs, but he cried lies, and refused"
  20,57,"Hast thou come, Moses,' he said, 'to expel us out of our land"
  20,58,"by thy sorcery? We shall assuredly bring thee sorcery the like of it; therefore appoint a tryst between us and thee, a place mutually agreeable, and we shall not fail it, neither thou"
  20,59,Your tryst shall be upon the Feast Day.' said Moses. 'Let the people be mustered at the high noon
  20,60,"Pharaoh then withdrew, and gathered his guile. Thereafter he came again"
  20,61,"and Moses said to them, 'O beware! Forge not a lie against God, lest He destroy you with a chastisement. Whoso forges has ever failed"
  20,62,"And they disputed upon their plan between them, and communed secretly"
  20,63,"saying, 'These two men are sorcerers and their purpose is to expel you out of your land by their sorcery, and to extirpate your justest way"
  20,64,So gather your guile; then come in battle-line. Whoever today gains the upper hand shall surely prosper
  20,65,"They said, 'Moses, either thou wilt cast, or we shall be the first to cast"
  20,66,"No,' said Moses. 'Do you cast!' And lo, it seemed to him, by their sorcery, their ropes and their staffs were sliding"
  20,67,and Moses conceived a fear within him
  20,68,"We said unto him, 'Fear not; surely thou art the uppermost"
  20,69,"Cast down what is in thy right hand, and it shall swallow what they have fashioned; for they have fashioned only the guile of a sorcerer, and the sorcerer prospers not; wherever he goes"
  20,70,"And the sorcerers cast themselves down prostrating. 'We believe,' they said, 'in the Lord of Aaron and Moses"
  20,71,"Pharaoh said, 'Have you believed him before I gave you leave? Why, he is the chief of you, the same that taught you sorcery; I shall assuredly cut off alternately your hands and feet, then I shall crucify you upon the trunks of palm-trees; you shall know of a certainty which of us is more terrible in chastisement, and more abiding"
  20,72,"They said, 'We will not prefer thee over the clear signs that have come to us, nor over Him who originated us. Decide then what thou wilt decide; thou canst only decide touching this present life"
  20,73,"We believe in our Lord, that He may pardon us our offences, and the sorcery thou hast constrained us to practise; God is better, and more abiding"
  20,74,"Whosoever comes unto his Lord a sinner, for him awaits Gehenna wherein he shall neither die nor live"
  20,75,"And whoso comes unto Him a believer having done deeds of righteousness, those -- for them await the most sublime degrees"
  20,76,"Gardens of Eden, underneath which rivers flow, therein dwelling forever; that is the recompense of the self-purified"
  20,77,"Also We revealed unto Moses, 'Go with My servants by night; strike for them a dry path in the sea, fearing not overtaking, neither afraid"
  20,78,"Pharaoh followed them with his hosts, but they were overwhelmed by the sea"
  20,79,"so Pharaoh had led his people astray, and was no guide to them"
  20,80,"Children of Israel, We delivered you from your enemy; and We made covenant with you upon the right side of the Mount, and sent down on you manna and quails"
  20,81,"Eat of the good things wherewith We have provided you; but exceed not therein, or My anger shall alight on you; and on whomsoever My anger alights, that man is hurled to ruin"
  20,82,"Yet I am All-forgiving to him who repents and believes, and does righteousness, and at last is guided"
  20,83,"What has sped thee far from thy people, Moses"
  20,84,"They are upon my tracks,' Moses said. 'I have hastened, Lord, only that I may please Thee"
  20,85,"Said He, 'We have tempted thy people since thou didst leave them. The Samaritan has misled them into error"
  20,86,"Then Moses returned very angry and sorrowful to his people, saying, 'My people, did your Lord not promise a fair promise to you? Did the time of the covenant seem so long to you, or did you desire that anger should alight on you from your Lord, so that you failed in your tryst with me"
  20,87,"We have not failed in our tryst with thee,' they said, 'of our volition; but we were loaded with fardels, even the ornaments of the people, and we cast them, as the Samaritan also threw them, into the fire"
  20,88,"Then he brought out for them a Calf, a mere body that lowed; and they said, 'This is your god, and the god of Moses, whom he has forgotten"
  20,89,"What? Did they not see that thing returned no speech unto them, neither had any power to hurt or profit them"
  20,90,"Yet Aaron had aforetime said to them, 'My people, you have been tempted by this thing, no more; surety your Lord is the All-merciful; therefore follow me, and obey my commandment"
  20,91,"We will not cease,' they said, 'to cleave to it, until Moses returns to us"
  20,92,"Moses said, 'What prevented thee, Aaron, when thou sawest them in error"
  20,93,so that thou didst not follow after me? Didst thou then disobey my commandment
  20,94,"Son of my mother,' Aaron said, 'take me not by the beard, or the head! I was fearful that thou wouldst say, \"Thou hast divided the Children of Israel, and thou hast not observed my word"
  20,95,"Moses said, 'And thou, Samaritan, what was thy business"
  20,96,"I beheld what they beheld not,' he said, 'and I seized a handful of dust from the messenger's track, and cast it into the thing. So my soul prompted me"
  20,97,"Depart!' said Moses. 'It shall be thine all this life to cry \"Untouchable!\" And thereafter a tryst awaits thee thou canst not fail to keep Behold thy god, to whom all the day thou wast cleaving! We will surely burn it and scatter its ashes into the sea"
  20,98,"Your God is only the One God; there is no god, but He alone who in His knowledge embraces everything"
  20,99,"So We relate to thee stories of what has gone before, and We have given thee a remembrance from Us"
  20,100,"Whosoever turns away from it, upon the Day of Resurrection He shall bear a fardel"
  20,101,therein abiding forever; how evil upon the Day of Resurrection that burden for them
  20,102,On the day the Trumpet is blown; and We shall muster the sinners upon that day with eyes staring
  20,103,"whispering one to another, 'You have tarried only ten nights"
  20,104,"We know very well what they will say, when the justest of them in the way will say, 'You have tarried only a day"
  20,105,"They will question thee concerning the mountains. Say: 'My Lord will scatter them as ashes"
  20,106,then He will leave them a level hollow
  20,107,wherein thou wilt see no crookedness neither any curving
  20,108,"On that day they will follow the Summoner in whom is no crookedness; voices will be hushed to the All-merciful, so that thou hearest naught but a murmuring"
  20,109,"Upon that day the intercession will not profit, save for him to whom the All-merciful gives leave, and whose speech He approves"
  20,110,"He knows what is before them and behind them, and they comprehend Him not in knowledge"
  20,111,"And faces shall be humbled unto the Living, the Eternal. He will have failed whose burden is of evildoing"
  20,112,"but whosoever does deeds of righteousness, being a believer, shall fear neither wrong nor injustice"
  20,113,"Even so We have sent it down as an Arabic Koran, and We have turned about in it something of threats, that haply they may be godfearing, or it may arouse in them remembrance"
  20,114,"So high exalted be God, the true King! And hasten not with the Koran ere its revelation is accomplished unto thee; and say, 'O my Lord, increase me in knowledge"
  20,115,"And We made covenant with Adam before, but he forgot, and We found in him no constancy"
  20,116,"And when We said to the angels, 'Bow yourselves to Adam'; so they bowed themselves, save Iblis; he refused"
  20,117,"Then We said, 'Adam, surely this is an enemy to thee and thy wife. So let him not expel you both from the Garden, so that thou art unprosperous"
  20,118,"It is assuredly given to thee neither to hunger therein, nor to go naked"
  20,119,"neither to thirst therein, nor to suffer the sun"
  20,120,"Then Satan whispered to him saying, 'Adam, shall I point thee to the Tree of Eternity, and a Kingdom that decays not"
  20,121,"So the two of them ate of it, and their shameful parts revealed to them, and they took to stitching upon themselves leaves of the Garden. And Adam disobeyed his Lord, and so he erred"
  20,122,"Thereafter his Lord chose him, and turned again unto him, and He guided him"
  20,123,"Said He, 'Get you down, both of you together, out of it, each of you an enemy to each; but if there comes to you from Me guidance, then whosoever follows My guidance shall not go astray, neither shall he be unprosperous"
  20,124,"but whosoever turns away from My remembrance, his shall be a life of narrowness, and on the Resurrection Day We shall raise him blind"
  20,125,"He shall say, 'O my Lord, why hast thou raised me blind, and I was wont to see"
  20,126,"God shall say, 'Even so it is. Our signs came unto thee, and thou didst forget them; and so today thou art forgotten"
  20,127,So We recompense him who is prodigal and believes not in the signs of his Lord; and the chastisement of the world to come is more terrible and more enduring
  20,128,"Is it not a guidance to them, how many generations We destroyed before them in whose dwelling-places they walk? Surely in that are signs for men possessing reason"
  20,129,"And but for a word that preceded from thy Lord, and a stated term, it had been fastened"
  20,130,"So be thou patient under what they say, and proclaim thy Lord's praise before the rising of the sun, and before its setting, and proclaim thy Lord's praise in the watches of the night, and at the ends of the day; haply thou wilt be well-pleasing"
  20,131,"Stretch not thine eyes to that We have given pairs of them to enjoy - the flower of the present life, that We may try them therein and thy Lord's provision is better, and more enduring"
  20,132,"And bid thy family to pray, and be thou patient in it; We ask of thee no provision, but it is We who provide thee and the issue ultimate is to godfearing"
  20,133,"They say, 'Why does he not bring us a sign from his Lord?' Has there not come to them the clear sign of what is in the former scrolls"
  20,134,"Had We destroyed them with a chastisement aforetime, they would have said, 'Our Lord, why didst Thou not send us a Messenger, so that we might have followed Thy signs before that we were humiliated and degraded"
  20,135,"Say: 'Everyone is waiting; so wait, and assuredly you shall know who are the travellers on the even path, and who is guided"